        {
          "type": "data",
          "data": {
            "text/markdown": "<span class=\"markdown prose dark:prose-invert contents\"><h3 id=\"filtering\">Filtering</h3>\n<span class=\"paragraph\">The <code>filter_missing</code> decorator is a special case of a more general <code>filter</code> class decorator, which allows the user to specify tests which trigger the 'missingness' behaviour if they fail.</span>\n<span class=\"paragraph\">We will now briefly run through some illustrative examples where filtering comes in useful.</span>\n<h4 id=\"skipping-large-files\">Skipping large files</h4>\n<span class=\"paragraph\">As an example, we will consider a situation where one of the files in a configuration is very large, and we want to avoid loading it into memory.</span>\n<span class=\"paragraph\">This is easy to achieve by combining the already-familiar <code>filter_missing</code> with a custom filter applied to the <code>read</code> method, using <code>filter_read</code>.</span>\n<span class=\"paragraph\">We will demonstrate this by creating a subclass of <code>CsvFileHandler</code> from earlier.</span></span>"
          }
        }
      ],
      "console": []
    },
